# Implementation Milestones and Quality Bar

## Scope priority
- Finish Milestone 1 before expanding scope.
- Complete Milestone 2 core session criteria next.
- Attempt Milestone 3 only if Milestone 1/2 are stable and tested.

## Milestone 1 essentials
- Screens: Login, Home, Onboarding (5 steps), Settings.
- Onboarding global state: draft + current step + submit status.
- Theme state: light/dark with token-based styling across screens.
- Submit mock flow: loading, success, and error UX.

## Milestone 2 essentials
- Auth/session state includes expiry awareness.
- Route guard redirects expired/unauthenticated users to Login.
- On 401 from /me or /submit: refresh once, retry once.
- Refresh failure logs out user and keeps navigation safe.
- Preserve onboarding draft across session transitions unless intentionally cleared and explained.

## Persistence requirements
- Persist theme and onboarding draft/current step.
- Session persistence is optional; if implemented, use secure storage for tokens.

## Testing minimum
- Unit tests for session lifecycle transitions.
- One integration-style test for submit retry behavior.
- Prefer meaningful behavioral assertions over snapshots.

## Anti-pattern blockers
- No global state for everything.
- No hardcoded scattered color values.
- No silent failures.
- No broad rerender hacks instead of root-cause fixes.
- No logging of PII or token values.

